body:
@longdafeng 
Different tools may define different tab size,the tab size may equivalent to 2 or 4 or 8 spaces/characters.
Defined tab size to 2 spaces, will be much easier to convert Tab(4) to 4 spaces and Tab(8) to 8 spaces.

@HeartSaVioR Thank you for comment! So do you mean that it is necessary to keep supporting JDK6, 7? JDK7 and below are [no longer supported by Oracle officially](http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/eol-135779.html?ssSourceSiteId=otnjp). There will be no public updates about JDK7. 

I think it will cause a lot of cost to maintain outdated JDKs, but I want to hear some other opinions. 
Thank you.
